Version 0.2 (2003-07-03):
* User visible changes
- Whitespace in messages received, sent and displayed is now preserved.
- Hircules can be run from a non-tty (previously a call to getLoginName
  prevented this)
- Hircules now creates its own directory (".hircules/").
- The "/me" command has been added for writing ctcp actions.
- CTCP actions are now displayed properly.
- When users join a channel their "user@host" info is also displayed now.
- MODE changes should now be displayed properly.
- All channels are now logged to a log file in ".hircules/log/".
- Channel tabs are now numbered.
- Channel members are now tracked per channel.  Quit and nick change messages
  only appear now in the relevant channel.
- Private messages and public messages addressed to one (with "nick: ...")
  cause an audible beep.
- Public messages addressed to one appear also in a new virtual alert channel.
- Input in a virtual channel is now always assumed to be a command, ie it has
  a '/' prepended to it automatically.
- /join can now also be used to display a hidden channel, or to start a private
  conversation.

* Implementation changes
- Message middle and tail now stored as String's rather than a list of words.
- new modules added:
  - WordString to handle strings of whitespaced words
  - Config to carry configuration variables
  - CTCP now houses the ctcp quoting and dequoting functions
  - Debug provides debugging functions
  - Directories contains various directory utilities
  - Display temporarily provides Gdk.beep

* Build changes
- lambdabot support is now a build option.

Version 0.1 (released 2003-05-14):

* First public release
- tabs for channels
- tabs for private dialogs
- "raw" channel tab
- all channel tab
- support for a few common irc commands
